summary: I think what fucked me up the most about the unicorn store is that I was constantly waiting for the twist - she schizophrenic,...
body:
I think what fucked me up the most about the unicorn store is that I was constantly waiting for the twist - she schizophrenic, it’s all a big metaphor, a hallucination, someone tricked her and is now trying to sell her organs.

This tells me that I’ve been taught that movies can’t just be about a unicorns and the real world at the same time, if there is magic it’s just a side effect of the drugs. I’m used to seeing fantasy used to disguise a big twist in television, when I used to treat magic and fantasy as something substantial and natural. I’m mostly sad about how my belief in those things has died…

summary: Captain Marvel is the Long Kiss Goodnight
body:
Captain Marvel is the Long Kiss Goodnight

Holy crap I’ve just realised Captain Marvel *is* basically the Long Kiss Goodnight (which I’m watching right now) with all the swearing and the top end violence taken out and aliens, superpowers and a cat added!

Amnesiac female lead with two different names/personalities and hidden in need of activation secret utter badassery

Samuel L Jackson is the good bro sidekick and their growing friendship double act is the heart of the film

Ultimately the female hero wants to get back to her family - husband and daughter in this case, maria rambeau and her daughter Monica in CM.

She finds her personal truth and defeats the vile bad guy/former love interest, secret military group she once served and all those who have used and manipulated her.

She’s a hero who in the end is prepared to risk her own life without question to do what’s right and save people.

Both films have an amazing lead that elevates the whole thing to another level - so props to Geena Davis and Brie Larson respectively
